{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-js","path":"/webpack/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/webpack/"},"id":"2046e746-95bf-55bd-9f5e-ff866d68d971","html":"<h1 id=\"basics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#basics\" aria-label=\"basics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basics</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>it is a static module bundler</li>\n<li>it can handle css, images, different languages like typescript, etc</li>\n<li>e.g. we have javascript files depending on each other. webpack can automatically understand this dependency tree and accordingly minify the build</li>\n<li>installing webpack - <code class=\"language-text\">npm i -D webpack webpack-cli</code></li>\n<li>to run webpack, use <code class=\"language-text\">npx webpack</code> or create add a script in package.json <code class=\"language-text\">\"build\": \"webpack\"</code></li>\n<li>the default file webpack looks for is webpack.config.js</li>\n<li>the paths needed maybe absolute, and relative paths may not work</li>\n<li>webpackâ€™s configuration file uses commonjs import</li>\n<li>a basic webpack configuration file -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> path <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"path\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nmodule<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">entry</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./src/index.js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the main file / entrypoint</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">output</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"bundle.js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// output file</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">path</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span>  path<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">resolve</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>__dirname<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dist\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// output directory</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">mode</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"none\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"loaders\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#loaders\" aria-label=\"loaders permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Loaders</h1>\n<h3 id=\"image-loader\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#image-loader\" aria-label=\"image loader permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Image Loader</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>install the loader - <code class=\"language-text\">npm i -D file-loader</code></li>\n<li>configure webpack -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n <span class=\"token comment\">// specify the base path for assets</span>\n <span class=\"token comment\">// this works for both development and production</span>\n <span class=\"token comment\">// since it uses relative paths</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">output</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">publicPath</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dist/\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">rules</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">test</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token regex\"><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span><span class=\"token regex-source language-regex\">\\.(png|jpg)$</span><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">use</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"file-loader\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>now, the js files can use images as follows -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Dog <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"../dog.jpg\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ...</span>\nimg<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>src <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Dog<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nthe image has a hashed file name in dist, and the src attribute of <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;img /></code> is automatically set to it</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"css-loader\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#css-loader\" aria-label=\"css loader permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>CSS Loader</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>adding loaders for css and sass -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">test</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token regex\"><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span><span class=\"token regex-source language-regex\">\\.(css)$</span><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">use</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"style-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"css-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">test</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token regex\"><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span><span class=\"token regex-source language-regex\">\\.(scss)$</span><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">use</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"style-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"css-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"sass-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>now, we can import stylesheets in our js files as follows -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./hello-world-button.scss\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>in the above configuration, the order of loaders (inside use) is important, and they are invoked right to left. e.g. <code class=\"language-text\">sass-loader</code> converts sass to css, <code class=\"language-text\">css-loader</code> converts css to js and <code class=\"language-text\">style-loader</code> adds style tags</li>\n<li>note: node-sass provides node bindings to lib-sass, the c version of the sass preprocessor</li>\n<li>we need to add the packages <code class=\"language-text\">npm i -D style-loader css-loader sass-loader node-sass</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"babel-loader\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#babel-loader\" aria-label=\"babel loader permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Babel Loader</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>e.g. adding babel helps us use latest ecmascript features before they are implemented in browsers</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://webpack.js.org/loaders/babel-loader/\">adding babel</a> -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">test</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token regex\"><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span><span class=\"token regex-source language-regex\">\\.(js)$</span><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">exclude</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token regex\"><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span><span class=\"token regex-source language-regex\">node_modules</span><span class=\"token regex-delimiter\">/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">use</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">loader</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"babel-loader\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">options</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">presets</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"@babel/env\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"transform-class-properties\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nupto presets, it is pretty much a standard, we just add stuff to the plugins usually</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"plugins\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#plugins\" aria-label=\"plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Plugins</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>while loaders are used for pre-processing, plugins do heavyweight tasks that loaders cannot do</li>\n<li>why saving the dependencies with <code class=\"language-text\">-D</code>/ <code class=\"language-text\">--save-dev</code> is important - this way, they are not made a part of the build, otherwise it will increase our bundle size</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"terser-plugin\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#terser-plugin\" aria-label=\"terser plugin permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Terser Plugin</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>helps in minification / reducing bundle size</li>\n<li>webpack 5 comes with terser plugin, yet we need to install it if we wish to configure it</li>\n<li>install it - <code class=\"language-text\">npm i -D terser-webpack-plugin</code></li>\n<li>adding it -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">optimization</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">minimize</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">minimizer</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TerserPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>uglify js is the older alternative to terser plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"minicssextract-plugin\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#minicssextract-plugin\" aria-label=\"minicssextract plugin permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>MiniCssExtract Plugin</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>if we continue using the css / scss loaders as described above, they generate a style tag in the html itself</li>\n<li>ideally, we would want a different css bundled file</li>\n<li>adding the package - <code class=\"language-text\">npm i -D mini-css-extract-plugin</code></li>\n<li>adding it to webpack config -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> MiniCssExtractPlugin <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"mini-css-extract-plugin\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nmodule<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MiniCssExtractPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"styles.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nalso, replace <a href=\"#css-loader\">style-loader</a> with <code class=\"language-text\">MiniCssExtractPlugin.loader</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"browser-caching\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#browser-caching\" aria-label=\"browser caching permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Browser Caching</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>we can cache js files in browser to improve performance when loading pages</li>\n<li>this can lead to stale cache, which can be fixed by appending hash to file names. this hash is calculated from the contents of the file</li>\n<li>to do this, change the webpack configuration to -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">output</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"bundle.[contenthash].js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ...</span>\n<span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MiniCssExtractPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"styles.[contenthash].css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>since the file names of js and css files are dynamic in nature, we need to use html webpack plugin to automatically update the references to these files in the html file\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HtmlPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">template</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"src/index.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>to clear the build directory (set under the output key) before generating a new build, we can use the clean plugin, which comes with webpack\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">CleanPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"development-vs-production\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#development-vs-production\" aria-label=\"development vs production permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Development vs Production</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>the mode parameter can be set to <code class=\"language-text\">development</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">production</code></li>\n<li>it also sets the variable <code class=\"language-text\">NODE_ENV</code> to the same value, which we can access using <code class=\"language-text\">process.env.NODE_ENV</code></li>\n<li>why use separate files -\n<ul>\n<li>enables source maps automatically in case of development and disables it in case of production</li>\n<li>enables terser plugin automatically for production</li>\n<li>plugins like minify css extract can slow down builds. so, having them for development is not ideal, since we care about faster and not optimal builds. so, we can go back to using style-loader in development</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>we can change the scripts to for e.g. - <code class=\"language-text\">\"build:prod\": \"webpack --config webpack.prod.js\"</code></li>\n<li>webpack dev server helps with live reload. to achieve this, add the below configuration -\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">devServer</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">contentBase</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> path<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">resolve</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>__dirname<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dist\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">index</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"index.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">port</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">9000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">writeToDisk</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nand add the script - <code class=\"language-text\">\"start\": \"webpack serve --config webpack.dev.js --hot\"</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"multi-page-application\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#multi-page-application\" aria-label=\"multi page application permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Multi Page Application</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>we now will have multiple entrypoints, i.e. multiple main javascript files for each of our page\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">entry</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token string-property property\">\"hello-world\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./src/pages/hello-world/hello-world.js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string-property property\">\"dog\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./src/pages/dog/dog.js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>we might need to change generated bundled file names for js <a href=\"#development-vs-production\">and css in production</a>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">output</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"[name].[contenthash].js\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ...</span>\n<span class=\"token literal-property property\">plugins</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MiniCssExtractPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"[name].[contenthash].css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>we need to configure our different html files to import their respective bundled js using <code class=\"language-text\">chunks</code>. what goes inside <code class=\"language-text\">chunks</code> is determined via the keys under <code class=\"language-text\">entry</code>. we also need to change the generated filename using the <code class=\"language-text\">filename</code> key, since the default is index.html which would result in a failure in case of multiple templates\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HtmlPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dog.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">template</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./src/pages/dog/dog.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">chunks</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"dog\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HtmlPlugin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">filename</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"hello-world.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">template</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./src/pages/hello-world/hello-world.html\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">chunks</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"hello-world\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nmy understanding as to why we did not have to configure filename of css separately - minify css extractor plugin does the splitting of css into different files, but otherwise for e.g. in development we use style loader, which means css files are linked to js files automatically</li>\n<li>optionally, we want the common dependencies across our js bundles to be reused. if we do not do the below, both the generated bundles will for instance, have lodash. this optimization is needed for production only, so that clients only need to re-download our bundled js which is much smaller\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">optimization</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">splitChunks</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">chunks</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"all\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"module-federation-using-react\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#module-federation-using-react\" aria-label=\"module federation using react permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Module Federation (using React)</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>it allows us to import dependencies during runtime</li>\n<li>it is available out-of-the-box webpack 5 onwards</li>\n<li>version 5 of create-react-app uses webpack 5, but it is abstracted away from us</li>\n<li>find the cra example for module federation <a href=\"https://github.com/module-federation/module-federation-examples/tree/master/cra\">here</a></li>\n<li>we set <code class=\"language-text\">singleton</code> as true since we do not want multiple versions of some libraries to run at a single time. some candidates for this option can be react, react-dom, react-router-dom</li>\n<li>exporting is as simple as\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">exposes</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token string-property property\">'./app'</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./src/app.tsx'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>importing is as simple as\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-js line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token literal-property property\">remotes</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">child</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'child@http://localhost:3002/remoteEntry.js'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nand now, the container app can import child apps like - <code class=\"language-text\">import App from 'child/app'</code></li>\n<li>since the bundle of child would have to be loaded asynchronously, move the contents of index.tsx to bootstrap.tsx and index.tsx becomes <code class=\"language-text\">import('./bootstrap.tsx')</code></li>\n<li>we can wrap each child app with their own <code class=\"language-text\">React.lazy</code> error boundaries in the root so that the root app functions normally without all the components</li>\n<li>we would want to keep the histories of the root and child in sync. this can be done by passing the parentâ€™s history to the child apps. child apps can have a default of creating their own history if nothing is passed down</li>\n<li>we might need a common component library, and publishing it to npm would be ideal, e.g. think testing</li>\n<li>to handle typescript for child modules, a quick fix is to make a file modules.d.ts in the src folder and put a statement <code class=\"language-text\">declare module child/app</code>. for a better solution, we can use <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@module-federation/typescript\">@module-federation/typescript</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Webpack"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"2046e746-95bf-55bd-9f5e-ff866d68d971"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1037383464","1617985380"]}